article.headline: North Florida 70, Mercer 61
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- James Grimball had a double-double with 15 points and 11 rebounds to lift North Florida to a 70-61 victory over Mercer on Saturday. Chris Timberlake added 14 points and four assists and Stan Januska chipped in 18 points for North Florida (3-24, 1-13 Atlantic Sun Conference) North Florida came back from a 28-27 halftime deficit by shooting 52 percent in the second half. The team scored 12 of 16 free throws in the final 20 minutes. Mercer (11-17, 6-9) shot 36 percent and hit five 3-pointers, but the Bears couldn't contain the Ospreys inside, where they were outscored 32-10. Brian Mills led Mercer with 16 points, while Shaddean Aaron had 15.
